problem:
In triangle $ABC$, $AB = AC = 5$ and $BC = 6$.  Let $O$ be the circumcenter of triangle $ABC$.  Find the area of triangle $OBC$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.6 cm);

pair A, B, C, O;

A = (0,4);
B = (-3,0);
C = (3,0);
O = circumcenter(A,B,C);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(circumcircle(A,B,C));
draw(B--O--C);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, SW);
label("$C$", C, SE);
label("$O$", O, N);
[/asy]

solution:
Let $M$ be the midpoint of $BC$, so $BM = BC/2$.  Since triangle $ABC$ is isosceles with $AB = AC$, $M$ is also the foot of the altitude from $A$ to $BC$.  Hence, $O$ lies on $AM$.

[asy]
unitsize(0.6 cm);

pair A, B, C, M, O;

A = (0,4);
B = (-3,0);
C = (3,0);
O = circumcenter(A,B,C);
